'''Saonetsuhiko''' is a Japanese deity, ancestor of the {{ill|Yamato no Kuni no Miyatsuko|simple}} and key figure in [[Jimmu's Eastern Expedition]].<ref>{{Cite web |title=Encyclopedia of Shinto詳細 |url=https://d-museum.kokugakuin.ac.jp/eos/detail/id=9159 |access-date=2023-10-27 |website=國學院大學デジタルミュージアム |language=ja}}</ref> He was the first Yamato no Kuni no Miyatsuko.<ref>{{cite book |chapter=Book Ten Kokuzō Hongi |series=Brill's Japanese Studies Library |date=2006 |volume=25 |doi=10.1163/9789047418191_022 |title=The Authenticity of Sendai Kuji Hongi |pages=362 |editor-last=Bentley |editor-first=John R. |publisher=BRILL |isbn=978-90-04-15225-0}}</ref>
He is identified with Yamato no Sukune.<ref>{{Cite book |last=Suzuki |first=Masanobu |url=http://dx.doi.org/10.4324/9781315270852 |title=Clans and Genealogy in Ancient Japan |date=2017-02-03 |publisher=Routledge |isbn=978-1-315-27085-2 |pages=288}}</ref> [[ja:椎根津彦]] ==Genealogy== {{Descendants of Watatsumi}} ==References== {{reflist}} {{Miwa and Yamato Faith}}
